Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: udemy-dl
Version: 0.1
Summary: Download videos from Udemy for personal offline use
Home-page: https://github.com/gaganpreet/udemy-dl
Author: Gaganpreet Singh Arora
Author-email: gaganpreet.arora@gmail.com
License: UNKNOWN
Description: A script to download lecture videos for a udemy course.
        
        Install
        ~~~~~~~
        
        Udemy can be installed using pip
        
        ::
        
            sudo pip install udemy-dl
        
        If you don't have pip installed, look
        `here <http://pip.readthedocs.org/en/latest/installing.html>`__. Or if
        you trust me:
        
        ::
        
            sudo curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py | python
        
        Use
        ~~~
        
        ::
        
            udemy-dl -u email udemy_course_link
        
        Then you will be prompted for your udemy password.
        
        For information about other parameters, use the ``--help`` parameter
        
        ::
        
            udemy-dl --help
        
        
